what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
The command "ssh -i '~/UserKey.pem'" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com is used to establish a secure connection between the client and server. The command creates an SSH tunnel, allowing remote access to the server.
